ZH: 小猫喜欢爬树。
EN: The kitten likes to climb trees.

ZH: 他喜欢在周末爬山。
EN: He likes to hike on weekends.

ZH: 孩子们在公园里爬犁。
EN: The children are crawling on the playground.

ZH: 我们决定今天爬楼梯而不乘电梯。
EN: We decided to climb the stairs today instead of taking the elevator.

ZH: 猴子能够很快地爬到高处。
EN: Monkeys can climb quickly to higher places.

ZH: 这只蛇正在慢慢地爬过石头。
EN: The snake is slowly crawling over the rock.

ZH: 我们趴在地上爬过短距离。
EN: We crawled a short distance on the ground.

ZH: 他们打算在下午自行车爬山。
EN: They plan to go mountain biking in the afternoon.

ZH: 爬山是很好的锻炼。
EN: Mountain climbing is great exercise.

ZH: 这只猴子正在树上爬。
EN: The monkey is climbing on the tree.

ZH: 孩子们喜欢在沙滩上爬沙堡。
EN: Children like to crawl sandcastles on the beach.

ZH: 我们应该爬得更高一点，才能看清楚这里的景色。
EN: We should climb higher to get a better view of the scenery.

ZH: 豹子可以在树上爬很高很快。
EN: Leopards can climb high and fast in trees.

ZH: 柳树上结满了青蛙，它们会爬到树梢上。
EN: The willow tree is full of frogs, they will climb to the treetops.

ZH: 为了躲避危险，我们只能爬过悬崖。
EN: To avoid danger, we had to climb across the cliff.

ZH: 那些植物有时会爬上墙壁。
EN: Those plants sometimes climb up walls.

ZH: 猴子爬上了峭壁，并开始觅食。
EN: The monkey climbed up the cliff and began to forage.

ZH: 他们需要穿过密林并爬上山坡才能到达目的地。
EN: They had to pass through the dense forest and climb up the hill to reach their destination.

ZH: 这只松鼠灵巧地爬上了电线杆。
EN: The squirrel skillfully climbed up the utility pole.

ZH: 他偷偷地爬上了楼梯，希望不被发现。
EN: He secretly climbed up the stairs, hoping not to be discovered.
